    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="255"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 139.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 180, of November 3 last,
                    concerning the claim of the Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon, I have to say
                    that before the opening of the Peruvian Congress, which, as stated in your No.
                    180, will take place on July 28 next, it will be well to call the attention of
                    the foreign office to the claim, and to urge that it may be again recommended to
                    Congress.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
